1DESCRIPTION         top
2mq_open() creates a new POSIX message queue or opens an existing
3queue.  The queue is identified by name.  For details of the
4construction of name, see mq_overview(7).
5The oflag argument specifies flags that control the operation of
6the call.  (Definitions of the flags values can be obtained by
7including <fcntl.h>.)  Exactly one of the following must be
8specified in oflag:
9O_RDONLY
10        Open the queue to receive messages only.
11
12O_WRONLY